To use this script:

    Copy and paste the code above into a new file and save it with a name such as uninstall-docker.sh.
    Move the file to the directory where your .yml file or Dockerfile is located.
    Open a terminal in that directory and run the command chmod +x uninstall-docker.sh to make the script executable.
    Run the command ./uninstall-docker.sh to execute the script.
    Reboot your system to ensure that all changes are applied.

If you have any questions, feel free to ask ChatGPT.
